# Task 2 – Dual-Role IoT Monitoring System (Role-Based Dashboards)

## Overview

This project implements a **Dual-Role IoT Monitoring System** using the ESP32 microcontroller and FreeRTOS. The system separates patient health monitoring from hospital environmental monitoring by providing two logical dashboards. Medical staff can monitor patient vitals, while facility management can monitor environmental conditions. The project demonstrates multitasking, real-time sensor acquisition, OLED visualization, MQTT-based data simulation, and alert handling.

---

## Features

- Dual-role monitoring architecture
- FreeRTOS-based concurrent task execution
- Medical Dashboard
  - Heart Rate
  - SpO₂
  - Body Temperature
- Facility Dashboard
  - Room Temperature
  - Oxygen Level
  - Air Quality Index (AQI)
- OLED dashboard switching every 3 seconds
- MQTT topic simulation through Serial Monitor
- Real-time alert system using LED and buzzer
- Periodic data aggregation and summary reporting
- Modular and scalable system architecture

---

